{"title_page": "Aridane Santana", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|Santana|Cabrera}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Aridane\n| image = \n| fullname = Aridane Jes\u00fas Santana Cabrera\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1987|3|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vecindario]], Spain\n| height = {{height|m=1.91}}\n| position = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| currentclub = [[Odisha FC|Odisha]]<br/>(on loan from [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]])\n| clubnumber = 9\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[UD Vecindario|Vecindario]]\n| youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132009 | clubs1 = [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a B|Deportivo B]] | caps1 = 117 | goals1 = 38\n| years2 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs2 = [[Real Zaragoza B|Zaragoza B]] | caps2 = 32 | goals2 = 12\n| years3 = 2010\u20132011 | clubs3 = [[Universidad de Las Palmas CF|Universidad LP]] | caps3 = 35 | goals3 = 12\n| years4 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs4 = [[CD Legan\u00e9s|Legan\u00e9s]] | caps4 = 15 | goals4 = 1\n| years5 = 2012\u20132015 | clubs5 = [[CD Tenerife|Tenerife]] | caps5 = 130 | goals5 = 44\n| years6 = 2015 | clubs6 = [[Bangkok Glass F.C.|Bangkok Glass]] | caps6 = 16 | goals6 = 9\n| years7 = 2016 | clubs7 = [[CD Mirand\u00e9s|Mirand\u00e9s]] | caps7 = 12 | goals7 = 3\n| years8 = 2016\u20132018 | clubs8 = [[Albacete Balompi\u00e9|Albacete]] | caps8 = 68 | goals8 = 20\n| years9 = 2018\u2013 | clubs9 = [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]] | caps9 = 32 | goals9 = 10\n| years10 = 2019\u2013 | clubs10 = \u2192 [[Odisha FC|Odisha]] (loan) | caps10 = 14 | goals10 = 9\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| club-update = 22 January 2020\n}}\n'''Aridane Jes\u00fas Santana Cabrera''' (born 31 March 1987), known simply as '''Aridane''', is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Indian club [[Odisha FC]] on loan from [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]] as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Vecindario]], [[Province of Las Palmas]], [[Canary Islands]], Aridane finished his youth career with [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a]], making his senior debut with [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a B|the B-team]] in the [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|fourth division]]. He achieved promotion to the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|third level]] in [[2006\u201307 Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|2007]], [[2008\u201309 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|being relegated two years later]].\n\nIn the following years, Aridane did not settle with any team, representing [[Real Zaragoza B]] in the fourth tier and [[Universidad de Las Palmas CF]] and [[CD Legan\u00e9s]] in the third. In January 2012, he signed with [[CD Tenerife]] in the latter league,<ref>[http://www.tenerifedeportivo.com/2012/01/04/aridane-el-tenerife-es-un-club-grande/ Aridane: \u201cEl Tenerife es un club grande\u201d (Aridane: \"Tenerife is a big club\")] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029212846/http://www.tenerifedeportivo.com/2012/01/04/aridane-el-tenerife-es-un-club-grande/|date=29 October 2013}}; Tenerife Deportivo, 4 January 2012 (in Spanish)</ref> scoring 25 goals in 37 games in [[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|his second season]] (adding two from three appearances in [[2013 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B play-offs|the play-offs]]) to help the club return to the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|second division]] after two years out.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.laopinion.es/deportes/2013/05/07/aridane-13-goleadores/473950.html|title=Aridane y 13 goleadores m\u00e1s|trans-title=Aridane and 13 other scorers|publisher=[[La Opini\u00f3n de Tenerife]]|language=Spanish|date=7 May 2013|accessdate=20 December 2018}}</ref><ref>[http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2013/06/16/seleccion/1371391424_048509.html El Alav\u00e9s aguanta con nueve y queda campe\u00f3n de Segunda B (Alav\u00e9s hold on with nine and are ''Segunda B'' champions)]; [[Diario AS]], 16 June 2013 (in Spanish)</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://eldia.es/deportes/2014-06-04/1-grancanario-Aridane-Santana-partido-cien-Tenerife.htm|title=El grancanario Aridane Santana, a un partido de los cien con el Tenerife|trans-title=Gran Canaria's Aridane Santana, one match from reaching one hundred with Tenerife|publisher=[[El D\u00eda (Canary Islands)|El D\u00eda]]|language=Spanish|date=4 June 2014|accessdate=12 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nAridane played his first professional match on 1 September 2013, featuring the last 27 minutes of a 0\u20132 away loss to [[CD Mirand\u00e9s]].<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2013/09/01/futbol/2adivision/1378063714.html El Mirand\u00e9s quiso y pudo (Mirand\u00e9s wanted it and got it)]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 1 September 2013 (in Spanish)</ref> He scored his first goal seven days later, in a 2\u20132 home draw against [[FC Barcelona B]].<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2013/09/08/futbol/2adivision/1378667716.html Un entusiasta Tenerife no pudo pasar del empate ante el Bar\u00e7a B (Enthusiastic Tenerife could not earn more than a draw against Bar\u00e7a B)]; Marca, 8 September 2013 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nOn 6 July 2015, aged 28, Aridane terminated his contract with Tenerife and moved abroad for the first time in his career, after agreeing to a two-year deal with [[Bangkok Glass F.C.]] in Thailand.<ref>[http://www.goal.com/th/news/4280/%E0%B8%9F%E0%B8%B8%E0%B8%95%E0%B8%9A%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A5%E0%B9%84%E0%B8%97%E0%B8%A2/2015/07/06/13351982/%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%B7%E0%B9%88%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B0%E0%B8%97%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%87%E0%B9%82%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%A1%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%99%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%9A%E0%B8%B5%E0%B8%88%E0%B8%B5%E0%B8%9B%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%B5%E0%B8%A5%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%A2%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%A9%E0%B9%8C%E0%B8%AA%E0%B9%80%E0%B8%9B%E0%B8%99?ICID=HP_TS_5 \u0e2a\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e34\u0e07\u0e42\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e31\u0e01!\u0e1a\u0e35\u0e08\u0e35\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e14\u0e35\u0e25\u0e2b\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e22\u0e31\u0e01\u0e29\u0e4c\u0e2a\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e19 (Bangkok Glass sign forward from Spanish giants)]; [[Goal (website)|Goal]], 6 July 2015 (in Thai)</ref> On 1 February of the following year he returned to his home country, signing a short-term deal with [[CD Mirand\u00e9s]] in the second division.<ref>[http://www.cdmirandes.com/noticia/aridane-santana-nuevo-jugador-del-c-d-mirandes Aridane Santana, nuevo jugador del C.D. Mirand\u00e9s (Aridane Santana, new player of C.D. Mirand\u00e9s)]; CD Mirand\u00e9s, 1 February 2016 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nOn 3 August 2016, Aridane joined [[Albacete Balompi\u00e9]], [[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|recently relegated to the third tier]].<ref>[http://www.albacetebalompie.es/aridane-santana-nuevo-jugador-del-alb/ Aridane Santana nuevo jugador del Alba (Aridane Santana new player of ''Alba'')] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917062651/http://www.albacetebalompie.es/aridane-santana-nuevo-jugador-del-alb/|date=17 September 2016}}; Albacete Balompi\u00e9, 3 August 2016 (in Spanish)</ref> In [[2016\u201317 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|his first season]] in [[Castilla-La Mancha]], he contributed 17 goals in 42 matches as his team were promoted as champions,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://as.com/futbol/2017/05/24/mas_futbol/1495629550_626686.html|title=El gol en el Albacete tiene conexi\u00f3n canaria|trans-title=Goal at Albacete has a Canarian connection|publisher=Diario AS|first=Juan Manuel|last=Sevilla|language=Spanish|date=24 May 2017|accessdate=12 September 2018}}</ref> including the extra time winner in the [[2017 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B play-offs|play-off]] semi-final against [[CD Atl\u00e9tico Baleares]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.es/espana/castilla-la-mancha/abci-albacete-llega-final-para-ascenso-tras-dramatica-prorroga-201706111912_noticia.html|title=2\u20131: El Albacete llega a la final para el ascenso tras una dram\u00e1tica pr\u00f3rroga|trans-title=2\u20131: Albacete arrive in the promotion final after dramatic extra time|publisher=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|language=Spanish|date=11 June 2017|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|100288|Aridane}}\n*{{LaPreferente|73674|Aridane}}\n*{{Soccerway|aridane-jesus-santana-cabrera/61673|Aridane}}\n\n{{Odisha FC squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aridane Santana}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Gran Canaria]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Canarian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Deportivo Fabril players]]\n[[Category:Real Zaragoza B players]]\n[[Category:Universidad de Las Palmas CF footballers]]\n[[Category:CD Legan\u00e9s players]]\n[[Category:CD Tenerife players]]\n[[Category:CD Mirand\u00e9s footballers]]\n[[Category:Albacete Balompi\u00e9 players]]\n[[Category:Cultural Leonesa footballers]]\n[[Category:Thai League 1 players]]\n[[Category:BG Pathum United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Indian Super League players]]\n[[Category:Odisha FC players]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in India]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name|Santana|Cabrera}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Aridane\n| image = \n| fullname = Aridane Jes\u00fas Santana Cabrera\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1987|3|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vecindario]], Spain\n| height = {{height|m=1.91}}\n| position = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| currentclub = [[Odisha FC|Odisha]]<br/>(on loan from [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]])\n| clubnumber = 9\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[UD Vecindario|Vecindario]]\n| youthyears2 = | you