ounded to nearest 10 thousand.</ref>\n| 40,000\u2013300,000 deaths.The death toll is disputed, ranging from some Japanese claims of several hundred,<ref>[[Masaaki Tanaka]] claims that very few citizens were killed, and that the massacre is in fact a fabrication in his book ''[http://www.ne.jp/asahi/unko/tamezou/nankin/whatreally/ \u201cNankin gyakusatsu\u201d no kyok\u014d] (The \"Nanking Massacre\" as Fabrication)''.</ref> to the Chinese claim of a non-combatant death toll of 300,000.<ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/2001/0820/p1s3-woap.html \"Why the past still separates China and Japan\"] Robert Marquand (August 20, 2001) Christian Science Monitor. States an estimate of 300,000 dead.</ref> Most other nations believe the death toll to be between 150,000\u2013300,000, based on the [[Nanjing War Crimes Tribunal]] verdict.\n|-\n|[[Changjiao massacre]]\n|1943, May 9\u201312\n|[[Changjiao]], [[Hunan]]\n|{{ntsh|30000}}30,000\n|\n|-\n|[[February 28 incident]]\n|1947, February 28\u2013May 16\n|[[Taiwan Province|Taiwan]]\n|5,000 to 28,000\n|Beginning of the [[White Terror (Taiwan)|White Terror]] campaign. The Chinese Kuomintang-led government imposed [[Martial law in Taiwan|martial law]] until 1987.\n|}\n\n== People's Republic of China (since 1949) ==\n\n=== 1949\u20131966 ===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!Name\n!Date\n!Location\n!Deaths\n!Notes\n|-\n|[[Chinese Land Reform]]\n|1948-1951\n|Nationwide\n|1,000,000 \u2013 4,500,000\n|Liquidation of the landlord class in [[struggle sessions]].\n|-\n|[[Campaign to Suppress Counterrevolutionaries]]\n|1950\u20131951\n|Nationwide\n|{{nts|1200000}}<ref>Geometric mean 712,000 and 2 million rounded to nearest 100 thousand.</ref>\n|712,000<ref name=\"Yang Kuisong\">{{cite journal|author=[[Yang Kuisong]]|year=2008|title=Reconsidering the Campaign to Suppress Counterrevolutionaries|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=1809176|journal=[[The China Quarterly]]|volume=193|pages=102\u2013121|doi=10.1017/S0305741008000064}}{{paywall}}[https://chinachange.org/2011/11/28/reconsidering-the-campaign-to-suppress-counterrevolutionaries/ summary] at China Change blog</ref> to 2,000,000<ref name=\"Mao's Killing Quotas\">{{cite web|url=http://hrichina.org/public/PDFs/CRF.4.2005/CRF-2005-4_Quota.pdf|title=Mao's \"Killing Quotas.\" Human Rights in China (HRIC). 26 September 2005, at Shandong University|last=Changyu|first=Li|format=PDF|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090729194758/http://www.hrichina.org/public/PDFs/CRF.4.2005/CRF-2005-4_Quota.pdf|archivedate=29 July 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Three-anti and Five-anti Campaigns]]\n|1951-1952\n|Nationwide\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Anti-Rightist Campaign]]\n|1957\n|Nationwide\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Socialist Education Movement]]\n|1963\n|Nationwide\n|77,560<ref>{{Cite book|last=Yang|first=Jishen|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4d4qDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT67&lpg=PT67&dq=%E5%9B%9B%E6%B8%85%E8%BF%90%E5%8A%A8+77560&source=bl&ots=225yUBw_7e&sig=ACfU3U0ulCZv1-yRXfQDGSL6XMBILQ8aDw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjZy5-opK3nAhWAl3IEHeEpAF0Q6AEwAHoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=%E5%9B%9B%E6%B8%85%E8%BF%90%E5%8A%A8%2077560&f=false|title=\u5929\u5730\u7ffb\u8986: \u4e2d\u56fd\u6587\u5316\u5927\u9769\u547d\u5386\u53f2|date=2017-07-04|publisher=\u5929\u5730\u56fe\u4e66|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=zh}}</ref>\n|\n|}\n\n=== 1966\u20131976 (Cultural Revolution massacres) ===\nSome of the massacres may have occurred during the [[Violent Struggle|Violent Struggles]] (300,000-500,000 deaths), [[Struggle session|struggle sessions]] or political purges.\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!Name\n!Date\n!Location\n!Deaths\n!Notes\n|-\n|[[Red August]]\n|August \u2013 September 1966\n|[[Beijing]]\n|1,772<ref>{{Cite news|last=Phillips|first=Tom|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/may/11/the-cultural-revolution-50-years-on-all-you-need-to-know-about-chinas-political-convulsion|title=The Cultural Revolution: all you need to know about China's political convulsion|da